 ernest w mcfarland professor of law and director of the stanford center on the legal profession at the stanford law school a lawyer and long time advocate for gender equality rhode's prominent voice as a researcher and academic successfully led the effort to create stanford's center on ethics the second kathryn stoner weiss is deputy director of the center on democracy development and the rule of law and senior fellow at the freeman spogli institute her work has focused on the political economy of developing countries transitions from authoritarianism as well as russian politics the program on social entrepreneurship is housed at the center on democracy development and the rule of law but is designed as a stanford wide initiative it benefits tremendously from a founding cross disciplinary faculty advisory committee who help shape and more fully develop close working relationships with partners across campus including the center for social innovation at the graduate school of business gsb the haas center for public service the center for philanthropy and civil society pacs the clayman institute for gender research the center for the legal professions at stanford law school the medical school's global health initiative search more information kavita n ramdas executive director for program on social entrepreneurship kathryn stoner weiss deputy director cddrl and senior fellow fsi support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4610 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
